E AFRICAN LIBRARY ASSOCIATION OF SOUTH AFRICA-ITS ROLE ON THE BLACK LIBRARYSCENE.     THE AFRICAN LIBRARY ASSOCIATION OF SOUTH AFRICA HAS BEEN IN EXISTENCE FOR 17YEARS. DURING THIS PERIOD IT HAS CONCERNED ITSELF WITH THE PROMOTION OF THEREADING HABIT AMONG BLACKS AND WITH THE UPGRADING OF THE QUALITY OF PERSONSENGAGED IN LIBRARY WORK BY MEANS OF VACATION SCHOOLS AND SEMINARS. IT HAS MADEREPRESENTATIONS TO LOCAL AUTHORITIES AND THE GOVERNMENT AND ALL THOSECONCERNED WITH THE PROVISION OF LIBRARY SERVICES FOR BLACKS, EITHER TO STARTLIBRARY SERVICES WHERE THESE WERE NOT IN EXISTENCE OR TO IMPROVE THE EXISTINGONES FOR THE BENEFIT OF THE LOCAL INHABITANTS